comments.body:
@jordigilh, thanks for reaching out!

Yes, you found the problem.  In order to manage the containers they must be started by systemd.  If the containers were started outside of the systemd units, systemd will complain.

Starting with Podman v4.2, you can run Kubernertes YAML directly in systemd: https://github.com/containers/podman/blob/main/docs/source/markdown/podman-generate-systemd.1.md#kubernetes-integration
